article.headline: Ark.-Pine Bluff 64, SMU 62
article.story: DALLAS -- Terrance Calvin hit four straight field goals as Arkansas-Pine Bluff came from behind Monday night to beat SMU 64-62. Calvin scored nine points over a 2:40 span to pull Arkansas-Pine Bluff to within one at 62-61 with 13 seconds left. Eric Brooks hit a jumper and free throw to seal the Golden Lions first win of the season. Calvin led Arkansas-Pine Bluff with 19 points. Lebaron Weathers had 18 for the Golden Lions (1-7). Paul McCoy led SMU (3-4) with 15 points. Papa Dia had 11 while Derek Williams and Mike Walker each added nine. Robert Nyakundi had eight points and seven rebounds for the Mustangs. Arkansas-Pine Bluff led 29-28 at the half. SMU led by nine at 61-62 before Calvin went on his scoring spree.
